OL,3,CCrews remain on site after fire on ship
OL,5,FThe service said there is no risk to
OL,6,Fthe public, and operations are being
OL,7,Fsafely scaled back.
OL,9,FChris Hadfield, Head of Operational
OL,10,FRisk Management for South Wales Fire
OL,11,Fand Rescue Service, said:
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/4
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1777320354
OL,3,CCrews remain on site after fire on ship
OL,5,F"Our crews have worked exceptionally
OL,6,Fhard throughout the day to bring this
OL,7,Fcomplex incident under control. While
OL,8,Fthe situation is now stable, a fire
OL,9,Fservice presence will remain at
OL,10,FNewport Docks to monitor conditions
OL,11,Fand ensure the fire does not reignite.
OL,12,FWe are grateful for the cooperation
OL,13,Fbetween our partner agencies and the
OL,14,Fpublic during this incident."
OL,16,FAt this time, the cause of the fire is
OL,17,Fnot known. Any further investigations
OL,18,Fwill take place as appropriate.
